tip.text: The big drawer is the outside seating and the atmosphere but you can sit inside to take in the vaulted sealing and access to quick service. The pretzels are fantastic. The hock is also great
The presa was fantastic. I still think about it
Sit at the bar if you want to enjoy the 2 for 1 cocktails during aperitivo time (5-7pm)
Sweet French pastries and bread, decent coffee
The small loaves are a steal and make great toast for a few days and the staff are lovely and keen on promoting a great sense of community. Love it
Fantastic breakfast menu - go for the range of refreshingly different choices
If you're sitting outside in the sun they have sunscreen!
The melting moments are the best I've tried. Huge and delicious
Lots of great, healthy options. Ask for more chutney if you get the green fritters
It's worth getting a little adventurous - stranger dishes (like popcorn duck tongues) are a surprising delight (as is everything). Excellent show case of pacific rim cooking and NZ produce.
Part of the schtick seems to be LOUDNESS. If you aren't down with that head across the walkway to the courtyard
Nice sitting up the front by the counter - particularly at the high table by the window if you just want to grab a coffee
A second schnitzel is only a few dollars more so order it and either enjoy two or share it with someone at the table who has schnitzel envy. Excellent with potato salad!
The lunch specials are great value and the flavours are authentic and deep
Bring some BBQ food and soak up the amazing scenery while the kids play in the playground
Lots of light from the amazing windows, still waiting for the garden and the kitchen but the signs are positive so far

tip.text: Published secret menu. Classic
Call and book for a tour, there's a good chance you'll be the only ones on it. If you don't want to do that you can still ring the bell and ask to do a tasting - very elegant sherry a and brandys
Try the apfeltorte with a crunchy, chewy topping and nicely spiced apples or the topfenstrudel (with whipped cream, vanilla sauce or ice cream). Excellent!
Room 8 is great
La flam's aux escargots is delicious!
The pork coming off the charcoal cooker is amazing!
